40
00:03:34,268 --> 00:03:36,119
<i><font color="#804040">ELEANOR</font>: Captain.</i>

41
00:03:38,789 --> 00:03:40,373
<i>Captain.</i>

42
00:03:41,458 --> 00:03:43,126
<i>Captain!</i>

43
00:03:44,578 --> 00:03:47,089
Sorry, you were asking
about the Scarborough?

44
00:03:47,114 --> 00:03:49,725
I was, specifically how the hell
did she find you out there?

45
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:52,645
A trap laid by your father,

46
00:03:52,670 --> 00:03:55,471
for which he will be answering
as soon as I'm finished here.

47
00:03:56,790 --> 00:03:59,151
He won't be the
only one, I assume.

48
00:03:59,176 --> 00:04:03,038
<i>Your friend Mrs. Barlow
understood she was responsible</i>

49
00:04:03,063 --> 00:04:04,740
for keeping him
under lock and key.

50
00:04:04,765 --> 00:04:06,542
You trusted her.

51
00:04:06,567 --> 00:04:08,043
We trusted her and
she betrayed us.

52
00:04:08,068 --> 00:04:11,964
Perhaps he managed to secrete
a message past her men.

53
00:04:11,989 --> 00:04:14,300
That hardly rises to
the level of betrayal.

54
00:04:14,325 --> 00:04:16,585
<font color="#808080">(SCOFFS)</font>

55
00:04:16,610 --> 00:04:20,455
Captain, yesterday morning,
my father walked into town,

56
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,124
stood out on the steps
of the warehouse

57
00:04:22,149 --> 00:04:23,976
<i>and proclaimed to the world
that the Guthries' business</i>

58
00:04:24,001 --> 00:04:25,844
is finished here in Nassau.

59
00:04:25,869 --> 00:04:27,429
What was the reaction?

60
00:04:27,454 --> 00:04:30,349
The men elected representatives,

61
00:04:30,374 --> 00:04:32,801
we agreed upon an agenda,

62
00:04:32,826 --> 00:04:36,262
and we spoke about the merits
of mutual cooperation over tea.

63
00:04:37,831 --> 00:04:39,308
So it was bad?

64
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,910
Bad? It was fucking chaos.

65
00:04:40,935 --> 00:04:43,779
- <i>Yeah.
- <font color="#804040">ELEANOR</font>: For about an hour,</i>

66
00:04:43,804 --> 00:04:45,698
<i>I thought they had burned
down all of Nassau.</i>

67
00:04:45,723 --> 00:04:47,499
But it's been handled.

68
00:04:47,524 --> 00:04:50,452
As of last night, I've
instituted a new trading system

69
00:04:50,477 --> 00:04:53,005
and the street has embraced it.

70
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:55,657
A consortium with
myself at it's head,

71
00:04:55,682 --> 00:04:58,510
Captains Naft and Lawrence
as a means of shipping,

72
00:04:58,535 --> 00:05:01,847
<i>and Mr. Frasier as
it's corporate seal.</i>

73
00:05:01,872 --> 00:05:03,515
Hmm.

74
00:05:03,540 --> 00:05:05,491
All this since yesterday?

75
00:05:07,711 --> 00:05:11,941
I will address the situation
with Mrs. Barlow immediately.

76
00:05:11,966 --> 00:05:13,633
<i>You have my word.</i>

77
00:05:15,469 --> 00:05:16,678
<font color="#808080">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

78
00:05:16,703 --> 00:05:18,480
Captain, one more thing.

79
00:05:18,505 --> 00:05:21,419
<i>The consortium wasn't
founded easily.</i>

80
00:05:21,444 --> 00:05:23,685
It required the assistance
of a few other parties.

81
00:05:23,710 --> 00:05:26,846
Among them indispensably
was Mr. Silver.

82
00:05:27,931 --> 00:05:29,658
Is that so?

83
00:05:29,683 --> 00:05:31,243
<i><font color="#804040">ELEANOR</font>: I tell you
this because I imagine</i>

84
00:05:31,268 --> 00:05:33,695
<i>you might still hold some
resentment toward him.</i>

85
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:36,165
And I've given him my word in
exchange for his assistance

86
00:05:36,190 --> 00:05:39,075
that I'll stand between
him and your resentment.

87
00:05:40,244 --> 00:05:42,504
In other words,

88
00:05:42,529 --> 00:05:45,207
if Mr. Silver doesn't
return from the Urca,

89
00:05:45,232 --> 00:05:47,834
you and I may find ourselves
with problems of our own.

90
00:05:51,839 --> 00:05:53,873
What a day I missed.

91
00:05:59,847 --> 00:06:01,547
Come on.

92
00:06:04,184 --> 00:06:06,102
<font color="#808080">(PANTING)</font>

93
00:06:14,478 --> 00:06:16,455
The fuck, Jack?

94
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:19,208
It's gone limp again.

95
00:06:19,233 --> 00:06:22,568
Really? I hadn't noticed.

96
00:06:23,937 --> 00:06:26,432
Well, do you want
something up your ass?

97
00:06:26,457 --> 00:06:28,583
No.

98
00:06:28,608 --> 00:06:30,209
No, thank you.

99
00:06:32,546 --> 00:06:34,464
<font color="#808080">(GRUNTS)</font>

100
00:06:37,051 --> 00:06:38,892
What the fuck is your problem?

101
00:06:40,530 --> 00:06:42,731
I'm terribly sorry if
I've ruined your morning,

102
00:06:42,756 --> 00:06:45,150
but at the moment I happen to
have quite a lot on my mind.

103
00:06:45,175 --> 00:06:48,237
Ship purloined, captain and
crew a distant memory,

104
00:06:48,262 --> 00:06:50,789
<i>no prospects at all,</i>

105
00:06:50,814 --> 00:06:52,708
except for this
shithole of a brothel,

106
00:06:52,733 --> 00:06:56,295
which by some miracle of economics
seems incapable of turning a profit.

107
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:59,498
How can you run a brothel
here and not make money?

108
00:06:59,523 --> 00:07:01,950
I have no fucking idea!

109
00:07:01,975 --> 00:07:05,445
Ain't you always the one telling
everyone how fucking clever you are?

110
00:07:08,832 --> 00:07:10,249
Figure it out.

111
00:07:12,035 --> 00:07:14,813
Don't you dare leave me here.

112
00:07:14,838 --> 00:07:17,632
- <i>Don't you...
- <font color="#808080">(DOOR SLAMS)</font></i>

113
00:07:17,657 --> 00:07:20,593
<i><font color="#808080">(DISTANT DONKEY BRAYING)</font></i>

114
00:07:30,687 --> 00:07:34,116
Alice made you her porridge.

115
00:07:34,141 --> 00:07:37,461
Thicker than snot, but it'll
help you get your strength back.

116
00:07:41,865 --> 00:07:44,826
A couple of us are wondering
what you plan to do now.

117
00:07:44,851 --> 00:07:46,962
Why would anyone care what I do?

118
00:07:46,987 --> 00:07:49,548
Darling, you're all anyone's
talking about out there.

119
00:07:49,573 --> 00:07:51,600
All of us wondering what
kind of voodoo you used

120
00:07:51,625 --> 00:07:54,169
to get eight of Vane's
crew to just...

121
00:07:54,194 --> 00:07:55,721
up and disappear.

122
00:07:55,746 --> 00:07:58,307
Haven't you heard?

123
00:07:58,332 --> 00:08:00,275
They left for Port Royal.

124
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:02,620
Hmm, and I'm Henry
fuckin' Avery.

125
00:08:05,593 --> 00:08:08,033
If you've got any thought
of working here again,

126
00:08:08,058 --> 00:08:10,369
- I wouldn't wait too long.
- What do you mean?

127
00:08:10,394 --> 00:08:13,038
Mr. Rackham's got no idea
how to run this place.

128
00:08:13,063 --> 00:08:14,689
We've all got a
hand in his pocket.

129
00:08:14,714 --> 00:08:16,191
<i>Mapleton would tell him,</i>

130
00:08:16,216 --> 00:08:18,193
but she's too busy
stealing for herself.

131
00:08:18,218 --> 00:08:21,580
<i><font color="#804040">MAPLETON</font>: Idelle! Downstairs.
Customer.</i>

132
00:08:21,605 --> 00:08:24,607
All I'm saying is get in
while the getting's good.

133
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:28,494
<i><font color="#808080">(DOOR CLOSES)</font></i>

134
00:08:31,398 --> 00:08:33,592
<font color="#808080">(GRUNTS)</font>

135
00:08:33,617 --> 00:08:37,045
Jesus! The fuck did
they do to you?

136
00:08:37,070 --> 00:08:38,764
<i>Postelection
initiation, I'm told.</i>

137
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:40,816
All done in good fun.

138
00:08:40,841 --> 00:08:42,317
At least... <font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>

139
00:08:42,342 --> 00:08:44,520
I think it was all
done in good fun.

140
00:08:44,545 --> 00:08:48,190
- Congratulations, Mr. Quartermaster.
- Thank you.

141
00:08:48,215 --> 00:08:49,741
Unfortunate, to say the least,

142
00:08:49,766 --> 00:08:51,560
that we find ourselves
in the need of one.

143
00:08:51,585 --> 00:08:53,162
Yes, very.

144
00:08:53,187 --> 00:08:56,222
But I'm humbled by the
crew's faith in me.

145
00:08:57,414 --> 00:08:59,334
Well, if Billy were here,

146
00:08:59,359 --> 00:09:00,836
I'm sure he would agree with me

147
00:09:00,861 --> 00:09:03,038
when I say that the
crew chose well.

148
00:09:03,063 --> 00:09:06,199
Well, much to do.

149
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:12,080
Mr. Dufresne, quartermaster.

150
00:09:12,105 --> 00:09:14,183
Who would've seen that coming?

151
00:09:14,208 --> 00:09:16,385
- I think he's up to it.
- I'm sure he is.

152
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:19,555
