capable of coming to that conclusion.

153
00:09:19,580 --> 00:09:22,140
Well, chew a man's throat out,
it tends to make an impression.

154
00:09:22,165 --> 00:09:25,227
<font color="#808080">(BOTH CHUCKLE)</font>

155
00:09:25,252 --> 00:09:27,572
You'll be heading to
see her now, then?

156
00:09:30,807 --> 00:09:32,484
Mrs. Barlow.

157
00:09:32,509 --> 00:09:34,152
You said you'd be
holding her to account.

158
00:09:34,177 --> 00:09:37,313
I assumed you'd
not want to wait.

159
00:09:38,643 --> 00:09:41,043
I'll be back before dark.

160
00:09:41,068 --> 00:09:43,986
We'll continue preparations
for our departure then.

161
00:09:54,147 --> 00:09:55,674
<i><font color="#804040">GATES</font>: Just one more
thing, Captain,</i>

162
00:09:55,699 --> 00:09:58,677
before you leave to
see Mrs. Barlow.

163
00:09:58,702 --> 00:10:02,121
I think you and I need to discuss
the letter that Billy found...

164
00:10:03,707 --> 00:10:05,901
and why exactly it
is that she believes

165
00:10:05,926 --> 00:10:07,843
you're gonna betray your crew.

166
00:10:15,835 --> 00:10:17,812
- <font color="#808080">(GRUNTS)</font>
- Hey, get back.

167
00:10:17,837 --> 00:10:19,531
Jesus, Randall.

168
00:10:19,556 --> 00:10:20,749
<font color="#808080">(PANTING)</font>

169
00:10:20,774 --> 00:10:22,642
<font color="#804040">DE GROOT</font>: Mate.

170
00:10:25,979 --> 00:10:28,507
Randall would like
a word with you.

171
00:10:28,532 --> 00:10:30,926
- Council just voted. He's out.
- Out?

172
00:10:30,951 --> 00:10:33,295
<i><font color="#804040">DE GROOT</font>: I suppose
it's my fault.</i>

173
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:35,847
I raised the concern
about the fire hazard

174
00:10:35,872 --> 00:10:38,500
a one-legged man in the
galley might present.

175
00:10:38,525 --> 00:10:40,802
And like most things
before the council,

176
00:10:40,827 --> 00:10:42,304
it spun out of control.

177
00:10:42,329 --> 00:10:44,556
What's that got to do with me?

178
00:10:44,581 --> 00:10:46,892
He's got a raw deal, Mr. Silver.

179
00:10:46,917 --> 00:10:49,885
The least we can do is
let him say his piece.

180
00:10:52,673 --> 00:10:53,982
<i><font color="#808080">(SILVER SIGHS)</font></i>

181
00:10:54,007 --> 00:10:55,784
Randall.

182
00:10:55,809 --> 00:10:58,954
It's not fair. I can cook.

183
00:10:58,979 --> 00:11:02,624
Yes, I think you might
have mentioned that.

184
00:11:02,649 --> 00:11:05,577
You know, it's
been my experience

185
00:11:05,602 --> 00:11:09,798
setbacks such as these,
they often go hand in hand

186
00:11:09,823 --> 00:11:12,501
<i>with new and unexpected
opportunities.</i>

187
00:11:12,526 --> 00:11:13,776
He's a thief.

188
00:11:17,864 --> 00:11:19,758
What are you talking
about, Randall?

189
00:11:19,783 --> 00:11:24,062
He thought I was asleep
at Miss Guthrie's tavern.

190
00:11:24,087 --> 00:11:26,815
<i>I heard him talking.</i>

191
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:30,209
Wasn't Singleton stole
the page, it was him.

192
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:37,025
I don't know what
he's talking about.

193
00:11:37,050 --> 00:11:40,862
Randall, are you being truthful?

194
00:11:40,887 --> 00:11:43,832
He said he has the
schedule in his head,

195
00:11:43,857 --> 00:11:47,002
that he learned it to stop
Flint from murdering him.

196
00:11:47,027 --> 00:11:50,088
All due respect, but he
spent the last two days

197
00:11:50,113 --> 00:11:52,574
beneath a rather heavy
cloud of opiates.

198
00:11:52,599 --> 00:11:55,951
- He doesn't know what he heard.
- Get the quartermaster in here.

199
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,788
Right now.

200
00:12:05,662 --> 00:12:07,639
Bear with me.

201
00:12:07,664 --> 00:12:09,749
<i>One minute, please.</i>

202
00:12:10,967 --> 00:12:13,061
Uh, apologies.

203
00:12:13,086 --> 00:12:15,247
<font color="#808080">(SNAPS FINGERS)</font> Give me it.

204
00:12:21,311 --> 00:12:23,479
Ah! Here it is.

205
00:12:25,065 --> 00:12:27,626
It is with great pleasure
that we shall now commence

206
00:12:27,651 --> 00:12:31,880
our inaugural meeting of the Guthrie
Frasier Naft Lawrence Consortium

207
00:12:31,905 --> 00:12:33,582
for the Purposes of
Shipping and Trade

208
00:12:33,607 --> 00:12:36,275
in the West Indies, Excelsior.

209
00:12:41,248 --> 00:12:45,093
Reginald, add to the agenda
discussion of a shorter name.

210
00:12:45,118 --> 00:12:47,479
Jesus.

211
00:12:47,504 --> 00:12:50,265
First item of business...

212
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:52,317
our maiden voyage.

213
00:12:52,342 --> 00:12:54,469
Captain Lawrence,

214
00:12:54,494 --> 00:12:57,963
the status of the
Black Hind, please.

215
00:12:59,099 --> 00:13:00,642
<font color="#808080">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

216
00:13:00,667 --> 00:13:04,196
We've begun alterations
to expand our holds.

217
00:13:04,221 --> 00:13:06,364
- <i>But as I predicted...
- <font color="#804040">O'MALLEY</font>: Ma'am.</i>

218
00:13:06,389 --> 00:13:08,116
A good number of the
crew have defected

219
00:13:08,141 --> 00:13:10,810
upon learning of
their new vocation.

220
00:13:12,813 --> 00:13:16,508
Any suggestions for a new source of
labor would certainly be welcomed.

221
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:18,043
What happened to you?

222
00:13:18,068 --> 00:13:20,879
I told him to get the fuck
out, but he wouldn't go.

223
00:13:20,904 --> 00:13:22,321
He who?

224
00:13:37,354 --> 00:13:40,115
<i><font color="#804040">ELEANOR</font>: Quite the story
I heard out there</i>

225
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:42,007
<i>from the Walrus' men.</i>

226
00:13:42,375 --> 00:13:44,536
They say you rallied the slaves

227
00:13:44,561 --> 00:13:47,122
in the Andromache's hold,

228
00:13:47,147 --> 00:13:50,099
single-handedly turned the
tides against Bryson.

229
00:13:50,954 --> 00:13:54,195
Imagine what they'd say if they
knew that you're the reason

230
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:56,260
that they had to chase that
ship in the first place.

231
00:13:56,273 --> 00:13:57,829
I would like the chance
to explain myself.

232
00:13:57,842 --> 00:13:59,408
I'm listening.

233
00:14:02,746 --> 00:14:06,374
What I did, I did out of love.

234
00:14:06,399 --> 00:14:07,950
<font color="#808080">(SCOFFS)</font>

235
00:14:07,969 --> 00:14:10,929
And with every intention of staying
here with you to help you find a safer,

236
00:14:10,954 --> 00:14:13,706
more settled life, a
life you deserve.

237
00:14:15,792 --> 00:14:17,853
It was not a betrayal.

238
00:14:17,878 --> 00:14:19,020
It was...

239
00:14:19,045 --> 00:14:21,106
It was not your
decision to make.

240
00:14:21,131 --> 00:14:23,275
My life is my own.

241
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:26,260
It's not Benjamin Hornigold's,
it's not Charles Vane's,

242
00:14:26,269 --> 00:14:28,747
it's not my father's
and it's not yours.

243
00:14:28,772 --> 00:14:31,473
Do you understand?

244
00:14:33,059 --> 00:14:35,394
You're right. I'm sorry.

245
00:14:36,696 --> 00:14:38,340
And what?

246
00:14:38,365 --> 00:14:40,425
Now you think you can
just waltz back in here

247
00:14:40,450 --> 00:14:43,730
and pick up from where we left
off like nothing happened?

248
00:14:46,656 --> 00:14:48,624
Where else would I go?

249
00:14:49,709 --> 00:14:51,627
I belong to you.

250
00:14:52,879 --> 00:14:55,581
Chattel property of
the Guthrie estate.

251
00:14:59,970 --> 00:15:02,922
You... you know I've
never seen you that way.

252
00:15:05,225 --> 00:15:09,595
<i>Eleanor, I must ask
a favor of you.</i>

253
00:15:17,737 --> 00:15:20,632
<i><font color="#808080">(BIRD SCREECHING)</font></i>

254
00:15:20,657 --> 00:15:23,609
<i><font color="#808080">(DISTANT CHOPPING)</font></i>

255
00:15:33,336 --> 00:15:35,170
He's waiting.

256
00:16:34,097 --> 00:16:36,181
Sit.

257
00:16:44,223 --> 00:16:46,358
You wish to do business?

258
00:16:49,279 --> 00:16:51,447
There's a place...

259
00:16:53,116 --> 00:16:55,810
there's a place not
far from here.

260
00:16:55,835 --> 00:16:58,880
A place fueled by plunder.

261
00:16:58,905 --> 00:17:00,565
A place of great wealth

262
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:03,518
run by it's crews
and flying no flag.

263
00:17:03,543 --> 00:17:06,271
I know of Nassau.

264
00:17:06,296 --> 00:17:09,274
What of it?

265
00:17:09,299 --> 00:17:10,775
She's weak,

266
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:13,778
<i>so she's ripe for the taking.</i>

267
00:17:13,803 --> 00:17:17,231
A man with enough strength
could get his hands

268
00:17:17,256 --> 00:17:19,784
wrapped around her throat
in a matter of hours,

269
00:17:19,809 --> 00:17:23,562
control the flow of
trade, get rich.

270
00:17:25,815 --> 00:17:27,459
My men are rich.

271
00:17:27,484 --> 00:17:31,236
Wood sells well and we don't
rely on the mercy of the sea.

272
00:17:33,106 --> 00:17:37,018
No man is rich who could have
a lot more by doing less.

273
00:17:37,043 --> 00:17:39,628
<font color="#808080">(FLIES BUZZING)</font>

274
00:17:42,082 --> 00:17:44,726
When you sailed as
captain of these men,

275
00:17:44,751 --> 00:17:46,928
they sacked Campeche for you.

276
00:17:46,953 --> 00:17:50,098
They sacked Cartagena for you.

277
00:17:50,123 --> 00:17:51,933
Give me a dozen of them

278
00:17:51,958 --> 00:17:54,727
and I will bring Nassau in line.

279
00:17:56,262 --> 00:17:58,597
What's your name?

280
00:18:02,268 --> 00:18:03,936
Charles Vane.

281
00:18:06,940 --> 00:18:08,907
I know that name.

282
00:18:11,444 --> 00:18:12,921
<i>These are my men.</i>

283
00:18:12,946 --> 00:18:16,341
<i>Why would I let any of
them call you captain?</i>

284
00:18:16,366 --> 00:18:18,343
Each man gets a share,

285
00:18:18,368 --> 00:18:22,347
plus one share to you in
tribute for every six men.

286
00:18:22,372 --> 00:18:25,299
That's a sizeable piece
of a fucking fortune.

287
00:18:25,324 --> 00:18:27,459
And all you need do is
give them your leave.

288
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:37,019
How did you know to seek me out?

289
00:18:39,189 --> 00:18:42,141
<i>Is my name spoken
as far as Nassau?</i>

290
00:18:44,811 --> 00:18:47,479
Is there someone there
that connects us?

291
00:18:49,866 --> 00:18:52,651
<i>Or is it something else?</i>

292
00:18:55,121 --> 00:18:57,039
The fuck do you care?

293
00:19:01,544 --> 00:19:03,745
Do we have a deal or don't we?

294
00:19:09,669 --> 00:19:12,004
Three men.

295
00:19:13,807 --> 00:19:17,952
My tribute... a share
for every three men.

296
00:19:17,977 --> 00:19:19,394
Four shares in all.

297
00:19:22,232 --> 00:19:23,849
Yes or no?

298
00:19:27,153 --> 00:19:28,963
You're not answering
the question.

299
00:19:28,988 --> 00:19:32,500
I'm trying to answer
the question.

300
00:19:32,525 --> 00:19:34,219
So you're saying she's lying?

301
00:19:34,244 --> 00:19:35,887
That the letter is
just a fiction?

302
00:19:35,912 --> 00:19:39,281
I'm saying that my relationship
with her is a complex one...

303
00:19:40,783 --> 00:19:43,845
that it's hard for me
to understand at times.

304
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:46,848
But what is clear is that she
desperately wants to leave this place

305
00:19:46,873 --> 00:19:49,934
and will say anything in order
to make me go with her.

306
00:19:49,959 --> 00:19:52,044
Oh, for fuck's sake, enough.

307
00:19:53,179 --> 00:19:55,523
This is what we do.

308
00:19:55,548 --> 00:19:59,393
You orate and you dissemble,
and I look the other way,

309
00:19:59,418 --> 00:20:02,247
convince myself
that supporting you

310
00:20:02,272 --> 00:20:04,232
is in everybody's interests.

311
00:20:04,257 --> 00:20:06,918
But not today.

312
00:20:06,943 --> 00:20:08,586
Not after what
happened last night.

313
00:20:08,611 --> 00:20:10,705
After what happened last night?

314
00:20:10,730 --> 00:20:13,282
What happened to Billy, Captain?

315
00:20:14,934 --> 00:20:17,578
He fell.

316
00:20:17,603 --> 00:20:19,963
Why? What are you
saying happened?

317
00:20:20,860 --> 00:20:23,101
He thought you saw us
all as expendable.

318
00:20:23,126 --> 00:20:26,938
- Expendable?
- Pawns to be used for your own ends.

319
00:20:26,963 --> 00:20:30,925
I have fought and bled
alongside my men.

320
00:20:30,950 --> 00:20:35,146
I have sacrificed more than you could
possibly know for their futures.

321
00:20:35,171 --> 00:20:39,617
I know what happened
on the Maria Aleyne.

322
00:20:39,642 --> 00:20:41,119
You told me the man you killed

323
00:20:41,144 --> 00:20:43,204
was reaching for a weapon.

324
00:20:43,229 --> 00:20:45,206
You told me it was self-defense,

325
00:20:45,231 --> 00:20:48,276
but there were no
weapons in that cabin.

326
00:20:48,301 --> 00:20:51,279
I went and I looked.

327
00:20:51,304 --> 00:20:55,616
And I still kept my mouth shut.

328
00:20:55,641 --> 00:20:57,502
I don't know why,

329
00:20:57,527 --> 00:21:01,789
but I know you used the crew
to assassinate those people.

330
00:21:01,814 --> 00:21:04,058
Men died that day.

331
00:21:04,083 --> 00:21:05,626
Our men.

332
00:21:05,651 --> 00:21:07,562
And I suspect there's
been other times

333
00:21:07,587 --> 00:21:09,630
when we've been
expendable to you.

334
00:21:09,655 --> 00:21:12,901
And if yesterday was
one of those days,

335
00:21:12,926 --> 00:21:15,436
then you and I have a problem,

336
00:21:15,461 --> 00:21:21,133
because Billy wasn't
expendable to me.

337
00:21:23,169 --> 00:21:26,138
He was a son to me.

338
00:21:27,697 --> 00:21:29,617
Then perhaps you
should have acted

339
00:21:29,642 --> 00:21:32,203
like a better
father towards him.

340
00:21:32,228 --> 00:21:34,289
What the fuck did you just say?

341
00:21:34,314 --> 00:21:36,674
You let his suspicions
run rampant.

342
00:21:36,699 --> 00:21:40,295
You let his paranoia fester
to the point at which

343
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:43,348
when he should have been focused
on the Scarborough's guns,

344
00:21:43,373 --> 00:21:47,602
he was focused on hurling
unfounded accusations at me.

345
00:21:47,627 --> 00:21:49,670
So I'm to blame for
what happened to Billy?

346
00:21:49,695 --> 00:21:51,172
Perhaps if you had intervened

347
00:21:51,197 --> 00:21:53,341
when he first came to you
with these fantasies,

348
00:21:53,366 --> 00:21:55,843
perhaps if you helped
him understand

349
00:21:55,868 --> 00:21:58,069
the world in which he lived...

350
00:21:59,839 --> 00:22:02,000
he'd still be here right now.

351
00:22:08,648 --> 00:22:10,182
Where are you going?

352
00:22:12,101 --> 00:22:14,019
I'm tired of this.

353
00:22:16,439 --> 00:22:20,275
I'm tired of the energy
it takes to believe you.

354
00:22:21,694 --> 00:22:24,363
To believe in you.

355
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:30,869
I'm taking this to the crew.
You're their problem now.

356
00:22:32,839 --> 00:22:34,539
I'm taking it.

357
00:22:38,594 --> 00:22:41,489
After the Urca has been secured

358
00:22:41,514 --> 00:22:44,299
and the money warehoused
before distribution...

359
00:22:46,602 --> 00:22:50,081
I intend to sequester
a portion of it.

360
00:22:50,106 --> 00:22:52,224
- Sequester?
- A portion of it.

361
00:22:54,858 --> 00:22:57,338
Every man on that crew
will still be richer

362
00:22:57,363 --> 00:22:59,707
than their wildest dreams.

363
00:22:59,732 --> 00:23:01,575
But you know as well as I do

364
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:03,577
that no matter how much
money they're given,

365
00:23:03,602 --> 00:23:06,180
they will drink, whore
and piss it away.

366
00:23:06,205 --> 00:23:08,749
Now, they have a chance at
something better than that,

367
00:23:08,774 --> 00:23:11,853
but it isn't gonna happen unless
somebody makes it happen.

368
00:23:11,878 --> 00:23:12,970
You're lying to them.

369
00:23:12,995 --> 00:23:15,223
And if I don't, who will?

370
00:23:15,248 --> 00:23:19,027
Everyone's lied to for
their own good...

371
00:23:19,052 --> 00:23:21,279
every mother who
tells their child

372
00:23:21,304 --> 00:23:23,614
that everything will be alright,

373
00:23:23,639 --> 00:23:25,700
every soldier who's
told by his commander

374
00:23:25,725 --> 00:23:27,268
that courage will
see them through,

375
00:23:27,293 --> 00:23:30,395
every subject who's told by...
His King?

376
00:23:32,982 --> 00:23:36,110
Is that what you are to us now?

377
00:23:36,135 --> 00:23:40,072
A sovereign levying a tax?

378
00:23:42,191 --> 00:23:46,003
If no one knows, everyone wins.

379
00:23:46,028 --> 00:23:48,622
- <i>Don't play games with me.
- I'm quite serious.</i>

380
00:23:48,647 --> 00:23:50,925
Who loses?

381
00:23:50,950 --> 00:23:52,477
Absent their worst instincts,

382
00:23:52,502 --> 00:23:54,762
their pride, their
greed, their suspicion,

383
00:23:54,787 --> 00:23:57,982
in the light of pure reason,

384
00:23:58,007 --> 00:24:01,135
who says no to this?

385
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:04,021
They'll be rich men
in a safe place

386
00:24:04,046 --> 00:24:07,549
rather than dead thieves
on a long rope.

387
00:24:10,553 --> 00:24:13,647
I'm gonna deliver them, Hal.

388
00:24:13,672 --> 00:24:16,308
I'm gonna deliver them
into something better.

389
00:24:21,364 --> 00:24:25,760
<i>I will sail with you
tomorrow to take this prize.</i>

390
00:24:25,785 --> 00:24:28,930
I'll follow your lead in battle.

391
00:24:28,955 --> 00:24:32,183
And I'll take your
orders as consort.

392
00:24:32,208 --> 00:24:34,302
But when it's done,

393
00:24:34,327 --> 00:24:37,671
you and I will quietly
go our separate ways.

394
00:24:37,696 --> 00:24:42,134
And I'll thank you
not to protest.

395
00:24:56,482 --> 00:24:58,993
No one else knows about this?

396
00:24:59,018 --> 00:25:01,629
Look, as far as I can tell,
it's just the three of us.

397
00:25:01,654 --> 00:25:03,697
<i>Then again, this is Randall
we're talking about.</i>

398
00:25:03,722 --> 00:25:07,201
If he had told anyone
else, we'd have heard.

399
00:25:07,226 --> 00:25:09,837
Does it make any sense to you?

400
00:25:09,862 --> 00:25:12,590
Well, Flint finding
that page on Singleton

401
00:25:12,615 --> 00:25:15,367
does seem awfully
convenient in hindsight.

402
00:25:16,619 --> 00:25:18,379
Jesus.

403
00:25:18,404 --> 00:25:21,549
A fine mess here, Randall.

404
00:25:21,574 --> 00:25:23,334
<i><font color="#804040">RANDALL</font>: You're a thief.</i>

405
00:25:23,342 --> 00:25:25,520
<font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font> Quite sure you're wrong.

406
00:25:25,545 --> 00:25:28,322
But the good news is it's not
too late to repair the damage.

407
00:25:28,347 --> 00:25:30,691
I know what I heard.

408
00:25:30,716 --> 00:25:32,243
Randall, you were doped.

409
00:25:32,268 --> 00:25:34,052
<i>You have no idea
what you heard.</i>

410
00:25:39,192 --> 00:25:42,286
Say you're successful in
convincing our friends out there

411
00:25:42,311 --> 00:25:44,589
to believe your story.

412
00:25:44,614 --> 00:25:48,459
I'm not sure you've given proper
consideration to what happens next.

413
00:25:48,484 --> 00:25:51,128
Do you think they'd just haul
me up in front of the crew,

414
00:25:51,153 --> 00:25:54,182
air your story, and
that's the end of it?

415
00:25:54,207 --> 00:25:56,100
No, Randall.

416
00:25:56,125 --> 00:25:59,420
I think you've forgotten
one very important detail.

417
00:25:59,445 --> 00:26:01,189
The money.

418
00:26:01,214 --> 00:26:03,774
That has to be
considered, does it not?

419
00:26:03,799 --> 00:26:06,444
If we go tell the crew now,
there's a very good chance

420
00:26:06,469 --> 00:26:09,780
they simply hang the cook
right along with the captain.

421
00:26:09,805 --> 00:26:11,816
If Randall's right,

422
00:26:11,841 --> 00:26:14,569
<i>that would be the end
of the Urca hunt.</i>

423
00:26:14,594 --> 00:26:17,121
Are you suggesting
we keep this secret?

424
00:26:17,146 --> 00:26:20,575
Lie to the crew? Right
along with Flint?

425
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:22,577
He's suggesting
that acting hastily

426
00:26:22,602 --> 00:26:25,112
could come with a
very hefty price.

427
00:26:25,137 --> 00:26:29,074
Even if I was convinced, there's
still Randall to contend with.

428
00:26:31,911 --> 00:26:35,389
Are you suggesting there's some
way to guarantee his silence?

429
00:26:35,414 --> 00:26:37,782
I can think of one way.

430
00:26:39,652 --> 00:26:41,729
- They wouldn't.
- Wouldn't they?

431
00:26:41,754 --> 00:26:45,566
A one-legged halfwit versus
a chance at a fortune?

432
00:26:45,591 --> 00:26:48,486
The odds are decidedly
not in your favor.

433
00:26:48,511 --> 00:26:52,023
Well, you were
confused or delirious.

434
00:26:52,048 --> 00:26:55,026
Take your pick, but
tell them now.

435
00:26:55,051 --> 00:26:57,144
Then even if they wanted
to go to the crew,

436
00:26:57,169 --> 00:26:59,280
they'd have lost
their Chief witness.

437
00:26:59,305 --> 00:27:01,389
And no one has to die.

438
00:27:06,562 --> 00:27:09,874
- You're a thief.
- I'm a thief. Right.

439
00:27:09,899 --> 00:27:12,843
Well, good luck, Randall.

440
00:27:12,868 --> 00:27:15,846
<i>It was nice knowing you.</i>

441
00:27:15,871 --> 00:27:19,767
<i><font color="#804040">ALBINUS</font>: For as long
as you sail with him,</i>

442
00:27:19,792 --> 00:27:22,637
<i>his orders are my orders.</i>

443
00:27:22,662 --> 00:27:25,797
And when your work is done,
this place will have you back.

444
00:27:27,416 --> 00:27:29,301
They'll serve you well.

445
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:43,348
<i>Is something wrong?</i>

446
00:27:59,248 --> 00:28:01,416
You were one of ours.

447
00:28:03,536 --> 00:28:05,920
You were just a boy yourself.

448
00:28:12,261 --> 00:28:15,013
Could not have been
easy coming back here.

449
00:28:16,132 --> 00:28:18,216
Must have taken great strength.

450
00:28:19,802 --> 00:28:22,062
<i>Go on.</i>

451
00:28:22,087 --> 00:28:23,855
Take these men.

452
00:28:25,024 --> 00:28:27,525
Make me rich.

453
00:28:46,495 --> 00:28:50,548
You don't know me,
but you once did...

454
00:28:51,667 --> 00:28:54,169
when I was the lowest among you.

455
00:28:56,622 --> 00:28:59,734
Now I've returned.

456
00:28:59,759 --> 00:29:03,344
And I offer you a chance
to be free of this place.

457
00:29:05,097 --> 00:29:07,148
I'm Charles Vane.

458
00:29:09,301 --> 00:29:12,880
And you were a strong crew once,

459
00:29:12,905 --> 00:29:14,749
<i>proper pirates.</i>

460
00:29:14,774 --> 00:29:17,001
Feared, as you should have been,

461
00:29:17,026 --> 00:29:19,754
before he dragged you
away from the sea,

462
00:29:19,779 --> 00:29:23,891
<i>before he convinced you to
live here like animals.</i>

463
00:29:23,916 --> 00:29:26,644
Because it suits his weaknesses.

464
00:29:26,669 --> 00:29:28,295
<i>There is a place
not far from here</i>

465
00:29:28,320 --> 00:29:32,983
where strong men live lives
of pleasure, not labor,

466
00:29:33,008 --> 00:29:34,652
a place where you

467
00:29:34,677 --> 00:29:38,355
<i>could be feared and
respected once again.</i>

468
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:42,300
Follow me, and I will
show you what life is.

469
00:30:10,379 --> 00:30:12,356
<font color="#808080">(PANTING)</font>

470
00:30:12,381 --> 00:30:15,800
Are you done? Are you done?

471
00:30:18,637 --> 00:30:19,838
Oh!

472
00:30:28,898 --> 00:30:30,565
<font color="#808080">(GRUNTS)</font>

473
00:30:40,659 --> 00:30:41,659
<font color="#808080">(GROANS)</font>

474
00:30:56,425 --> 00:30:58,376
I'm proud of you.

475
00:31:13,959 --> 00:31:15,560
Randall.

476
00:31:17,696 --> 00:31:21,032
I need a word with
Mr. Silver alone.

477
00:31:26,539 --> 00:31:29,049
- <font color="#808080">(LAUGHS)</font>
- What's so funny?

478
00:31:29,074 --> 00:31:31,602
Just that I warned Randall
something like this was coming.

479
00:31:31,627 --> 00:31:33,354
I wouldn't be so
sure about that.

480
00:31:33,379 --> 00:31:37,441
Mr. De Groot's inclined to
hand you over to the crew.

481
00:31:37,466 --> 00:31:39,527
He's given me exactly
five minutes,

482
00:31:39,552 --> 00:31:43,096
at which point he intends to call
council so Randall can share his story,

483
00:31:43,121 --> 00:31:45,533
after which our hands are clean

484
00:31:45,558 --> 00:31:50,011
and you are most
likely, well, dead.

485
00:31:53,649 --> 00:31:54,959
What's that?

