00:46:45,457 --> 00:46:47,374
<i>Crazy?</i>

734
00:46:50,545 --> 00:46:54,224
To put ourselves
through all this

735
00:46:54,249 --> 00:46:57,167
when the outcome's so uncertain.

736
00:47:00,338 --> 00:47:03,340
The outcome is only uncertain
for those who disbelieve.

737
00:47:06,311 --> 00:47:08,846
I believe in this place.

738
00:47:10,253 --> 00:47:13,293
And I believe if there's anyone
who can do what's necessary

739
00:47:13,318 --> 00:47:17,104
to make it something
better, it's you.

740
00:47:55,426 --> 00:47:57,644
<i><font color="#808080">(MEN SHOUTING)</font></i>

741
00:47:59,898 --> 00:48:02,375
<font color="#808080">(GRUNTING)</font>

742
00:48:02,400 --> 00:48:04,902
<i><font color="#808080">(CHICKENS CLUCKING)</font></i>

743
00:48:07,155 --> 00:48:10,099
Oi, where are you going?

744
00:48:10,124 --> 00:48:11,751
Eyes on Randall at all times...

745
00:48:11,776 --> 00:48:13,210
wasn't that the deal?

746
00:48:18,416 --> 00:48:20,133
<font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>

747
00:48:22,453 --> 00:48:25,114
Randall, you are a
fucking puzzle.

748
00:48:25,139 --> 00:48:28,368
Part of me thinks you must be the
luckiest halfwit in the colonies,

749
00:48:28,393 --> 00:48:30,010
the way this all played out.

750
00:48:32,263 --> 00:48:35,766
But part of me suspects there's
something else going on here.

751
00:48:37,652 --> 00:48:40,713
I'm forced to wonder if you didn't
orchestrate this whole little drama

752
00:48:40,738 --> 00:48:44,825
knowing it would corner me into
securing your return to the crew.

753
00:48:46,828 --> 00:48:48,504
I'm forced to consider
the possibility

754
00:48:48,529 --> 00:48:50,306
there is a lot more
of the old Randall

755
00:48:50,331 --> 00:48:52,749
in that head of yours than
you'd like to let on.

756
00:48:55,536 --> 00:48:57,847
That you're no halfwit at all,

757
00:48:57,872 --> 00:49:00,567
but a very shrewd operator

758
00:49:00,592 --> 00:49:02,185
who's managed to
gain the benefits

759
00:49:02,210 --> 00:49:05,379
of sailing with these men
while avoiding all the risk.

760
00:49:07,265 --> 00:49:12,445
That perhaps, just perhaps,

761
00:49:12,470 --> 00:49:15,055
you're a goddamn genius.

762
00:49:19,010 --> 00:49:21,311
<font color="#808080">(FARTS)</font>

763
00:49:33,408 --> 00:49:35,325
<font color="#808080">(MEN SHOUTING)</font>

764
00:49:58,182 --> 00:50:00,543
<i><font color="#808080">(CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)</font></i>

765
00:50:00,568 --> 00:50:03,329
Mr. Gates.

766
00:50:03,354 --> 00:50:05,072
Mr. Quartermaster.

767
00:50:09,605 --> 00:50:12,005
The crew seem in good spirit.

768
00:50:12,030 --> 00:50:14,698
All things considered.

769
00:50:19,003 --> 00:50:21,898
What about our friend the cook?

770
00:50:21,923 --> 00:50:25,208
It appears to be
resolved for now.

771
00:50:26,410 --> 00:50:28,438
Though I must tell you,
he discerned that I knew

772
00:50:28,463 --> 00:50:30,389
about the missing
page beforehand.

773
00:50:30,414 --> 00:50:33,359
He assumed Billy told me.

774
00:50:33,384 --> 00:50:34,994
I can see how he
might think that.

775
00:50:35,019 --> 00:50:37,396
I did nothing to
dispel that notion,

776
00:50:37,421 --> 00:50:39,699
though it may not take him
a long time to realize

777
00:50:39,724 --> 00:50:42,702
who it was that actually
brought me into this.

778
00:50:42,727 --> 00:50:45,755
Well, we'll have to
deal with our situation

779
00:50:45,780 --> 00:50:49,742
as it develops, won't we?

780
00:50:49,767 --> 00:50:50,767
Aye.

781
00:50:55,239 --> 00:50:57,300
There's something else.

782
00:50:57,325 --> 00:50:59,852
It's Messrs. Howell
and De Groot.

783
00:50:59,877 --> 00:51:01,521
Give them a couple of days.

784
00:51:01,546 --> 00:51:04,787
Once we're at sea, the work will
take their focus off Randall.

785
00:51:06,834 --> 00:51:10,947
Actually, it's not Randall
that's troubling them.

786
00:51:10,972 --> 00:51:12,639
It's you.

787
00:51:13,891 --> 00:51:16,152
Having had some time
to think about it,

788
00:51:16,177 --> 00:51:19,763
they're not certain that you're
up to doing what's necessary.

789
00:51:21,682 --> 00:51:24,827
<i>The lying we could forgive.</i>

790
00:51:24,852 --> 00:51:26,379
<i>Singleton we could forgive.</i>

791
00:51:26,404 --> 00:51:28,855
We could forgive all of it.

792
00:51:30,525 --> 00:51:32,409
But not Billy.

793
00:51:34,612 --> 00:51:37,164
<i>That requires an answer.</i>

794
00:51:39,450 --> 00:51:41,094
<i>When the time comes,
we need to know</i>

795
00:51:41,119 --> 00:51:43,420
<i>that you won't
stand in the way.</i>

796
00:51:45,840 --> 00:51:47,967
<i>I understand he's your friend.</i>

797
00:51:47,992 --> 00:51:52,596
But once we have the
money, Flint dies.

798
00:51:54,215 --> 00:51:56,216
<i>No argument.</i>

799
00:52:00,772 --> 00:52:02,806
Not from me.

800
00:53:07,438 --> 00:53:10,373
<i><font color="#808080">(RUSTLING)</font></i>

801
00:53:23,085 --> 00:53:24,765
<i><font color="#804040">ELEANOR'S VOICE</font>: You
could be strong again.</i>

802
00:53:24,778 --> 00:53:26,132
<i><font color="#808080">(GASPS)</font></i>

803
00:53:26,157 --> 00:53:28,024
<i>You could resist me.</i>

804
00:53:30,061 --> 00:53:33,706
<i>You could take this whole
fucking island from me</i>

805
00:53:33,731 --> 00:53:37,284
<i>if only you weren't
so goddamned afraid.</i>

